{
  "doc_id": "59707",
  "text": "Consistent with it, we did not observe any difference in sizes of TADs between gene-dense micro-and gene-poor macrochromosomes. We were not able to identify TADs in several smallest chicken chromosomes, because they are poorly represented in the current assembly of the chicken genome [CITATION_1] . Further improvement in the chicken genome assembly and physical mapping will apparently contribute to the analysis of spatial organization of these tiny chromosomes in interphase nucleus.",
